# More info: https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#dockerignore-file
#
# Ignore everything by default and re-include just what the build needs.
# Note: Docker BuildKit drops parent directories that have no kept files
# (legacy builder behaved differently), so we have to whitelist each
# directory we care about explicitly even if its contents are kept.
**

# Re-include Go source — kept files first, then re-exclude tests so
# the test files aren't copied into the image.
!**/*.go
**/*_test.go

# Re-include each source directory tree we want preserved.
!cmd
!api
!internal
!hack

# Module + workspace metadata
!go.mod
!go.sum
